result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyle R Tracy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kyle R Tracy is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kyle R Tracy was found guilty of Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin [Modifiers: PTAC], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).
  • Kyle R Tracy was found guilty of Possession of Controlled Substance [Modifiers: PTAC], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Each ct concur. After 18 mo, if def has completed all programs & PO agent submits a letter, def can terminate from prob early.

Maintain full-time employment/education or combination of or be seeking same, and treatment.
Defendant shall not use/possess drug paraphernalia and/or controlled substances without a valid prescription.
Court finds defendant eligible for expunction under 973.015 without any ATR's & no new charges.
Random UA & BA testing at discretion of agent.  Any other conditions DOC, Probation/Parole Department may impose.
